## 6. API Reference

Import `taskflow.bru` into [Bruno](https://www.usebruno.com/) for a complete runnable collection with auto-captured tokens and IDs.

### Base URL
```
http://localhost:8080
```

### Authentication

**POST /auth/register**
```json
// Request
{ "name": "Jane Doe", "email": "jane@example.com", "password": "password123" }

// 201 Created
{ "token": "<jwt>", "user": { "id": "uuid", "name": "Jane Doe", "email": "jane@example.com", "createdAt": "..." } }

// 400 — validation failed
{ "error": "validation failed", "fields": { "email": "must be a valid email" } }

// 409 — duplicate email
{ "error": "email already in use" }
```

**POST /auth/login**
```json
// Request
{ "email": "jane@example.com", "password": "password123" }

// 200 OK
{ "token": "<jwt>", "user": { ... } }

// 401 — wrong credentials
{ "error": "invalid credentials" }
```

All subsequent requests require:
```
Authorization: Bearer <token>
```

---

### Projects

**GET /projects** — list projects accessible to caller
```
?page=1&limit=20
```
```json
// 200
{
  "projects": [ { "id": "uuid", "name": "...", "description": "...", "ownerId": "uuid", "createdAt": "..." } ],
  "page": { "page": 1, "limit": 20, "total": 3, "totalPages": 1 }
}
```

**POST /projects**
```json
// Request
{ "name": "Website Redesign", "description": "Q2 project" }

// 201 Created — returns ProjectResponse
```

**GET /projects/:id**
```json
// 200 — project + all tasks
{
  "id": "uuid", "name": "...", "ownerId": "uuid", "createdAt": "...",
  "tasks": [ { "id": "uuid", "title": "...", "status": "todo", "priority": "high", ... } ]
}
```

**PATCH /projects/:id** — owner only
```json
{ "name": "New Name", "description": "New description" }
// 200 — updated project
// 403 — not the owner
```

**DELETE /projects/:id** — owner only, cascades to tasks
```
204 No Content
```

**GET /projects/:id/stats** — bonus endpoint
```json
// 200
{
  "byStatus":   [ { "status": "todo", "count": 2 }, { "status": "done", "count": 1 } ],
  "byAssignee": [ { "assignee": "Jane Doe", "count": 2 }, { "assignee": "Unassigned", "count": 1 } ]
}
```

---

### Tasks

**GET /projects/:id/tasks**
```
?status=todo|in_progress|done
?assignee=<userId>
?page=1&limit=20
```
```json
// 200
{ "tasks": [ ... ], "page": { ... } }
```

**POST /projects/:id/tasks**
```json
// Request
{
  "title": "Design homepage",
  "description": "Lo-fi wireframes",
  "status": "todo",
  "priority": "high",
  "assigneeId": "uuid-or-omit",
  "dueDate": "2026-05-01"
}
// 201 — returns TaskResponse
```

**PATCH /tasks/:id** — project owner or assignee only
```json
// All fields optional
{ "title": "...", "status": "done", "priority": "low", "assigneeId": "uuid", "dueDate": "2026-05-10" }
// 200 — updated task
```

**DELETE /tasks/:id** — project owner only
```
204 No Content
```

---

### Common Error Shapes

```json
// 400 Validation
{ "error": "validation failed", "fields": { "title": "is required" } }

// 401 Unauthenticated
{ "error": "unauthorized" }

// 403 Forbidden
{ "error": "forbidden" }

// 404 Not found
{ "error": "not found" }

// 409 Conflict
{ "error": "email already in use" }
```

---

## 7. Running Tests

Integration tests use Testcontainers — they spin up a real PostgreSQL container automatically. Docker must be running.

```bash
# From inside the backend directory
./mvnw test

# Or with Docker Compose already up, exec into a build container
docker run --rm -v $(pwd):/app -w /app maven:3.9.6-eclipse-temurin-21 mvn test
```

Tests cover:
- Registration (success, duplicate email, missing fields)
- Login (success, wrong password, missing token → 401)
- Full task lifecycle (create, list, filter, update status, delete)
- Authorization guards (401 on protected routes without token)

---

## 8. What I'd Do With More Time

**Security hardening:**
- Refresh tokens with short-lived access tokens (currently 24h is long)
- Rate limiting on `/auth/*` endpoints to prevent brute force
- Input sanitisation beyond `@Valid` (XSS on description fields)

**Data model improvements:**
- Soft deletes with a `deleted_at` column — safer than cascading hard deletes
- `created_by` on tasks (currently implicit via assignee)
- Optimistic locking on tasks (`@Version`) to handle concurrent edits cleanly

**API improvements:**
- `GET /users` endpoint for the frontend to populate assignee dropdowns
- Cursor-based pagination instead of offset (better for large datasets)
- `ETag` / `Last-Modified` headers for caching

**Observability:**
- Structured JSON logging (currently pattern-based)
- Micrometer metrics → Prometheus scrape endpoint
- Request tracing with correlation IDs

**Testing:**
- Contract tests (Spring Cloud Contract) to ensure the Bruno collection stays in sync
- Load test to establish baseline latency before any optimisation

**Architecture:**
- Extract a thin `domain` module with pure Java — no Spring deps — so core business rules are portable and testable without framework overhead. The current service layer mixes Spring transaction annotations with business logic, which works but creates coupling.